alert.note: Alert for Carver; Scott; Sibley (Minnesota) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued May 23 at 9:01PM CDT until May 25 at 10:00PM CDT by NWS Minneapolis
info.description: ...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Minnesota... Minnesota River at Savage affecting Hennepin, Carver, Scott and Dakota Counties. Minnesota River near Jordan affecting Sibley, Carver and Scott Counties. .Rivers have crested and will continue to fall this week. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL LATE THURSDAY EVENING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Minnesota River near Jordan. * WHEN...Until late Thursday evening. * IMPACTS...At 26.7 feet, The bridge at Scott County Road 9 and Carver County Road 11/Jonathan Carver Parkway will be closed. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 845 PM CDT Tuesday, the stage was 25.9 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 845 PM CDT Tuesday was 26.3 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage early Thursday morning and continue falling to 20.3 feet Tuesday evening. - Flood stage is 25.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 25.9 feet on 04/05/1979. &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
